<%- include("partials/header") %>

<main class="container">

<section class="hero-world">
  <img src="/images/hero-world.jpg" alt="Mac and Cheese Around The World">
  <h1>Regional Variations of Mac and Cheese 🌍</h1>
  <p>
    Macaroni and cheese may feel like a classic American comfort food,
    but cheesy pasta dishes appear in cuisines across the globe.
    From Swiss Alpine casseroles to Caribbean street food,
    cultures everywhere have their own take on creamy pasta and melted cheese.
  </p>
</section>


<section class="world-grid">

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/switzerland-alplermagronen.jpg" alt="Swiss Älplermagronen">
    <h2>🇨🇭 Switzerland – Älplermagronen</h2>
    <p>
      This Alpine comfort dish combines macaroni, potatoes,
      cream, onions, and melted cheese. It is often served with
      caramelized onions and a surprising side of applesauce.
      Originally eaten by Swiss mountain herders.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/italy-pasta-ai-quattro-formaggi.jpg" alt="Italian four cheese pasta">
    <h2>🇮🇹 Italy – Pasta ai Quattro Formaggi</h2>
    <p>
      Italy’s version focuses on rich cheese sauces using
      combinations like gorgonzola, parmesan, fontina, and mozzarella.
      The sauce is smooth and luxurious rather than baked.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/jamaica-macaroni-pie.jpg" alt="Jamaican macaroni pie">
    <h2>🇯🇲 Jamaica – Macaroni Pie</h2>
    <p>
      A firm baked mac and cheese flavored with Caribbean spices,
      evaporated milk, and sharp cheddar. It’s often served in slices
      alongside jerk chicken or fried fish.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/classic-mac.jpg" alt="Canadian Kraft Dinner">
    <h2>🇨🇦 Canada – Kraft Dinner</h2>
    <p>
      Canadians love boxed mac and cheese more than any country
      in the world. Known simply as “KD”, it’s a staple comfort food
      and a nostalgic favorite across generations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/france-gratin-de-macaronis.jpg" alt="French macaroni gratin">
    <h2>🇫🇷 France – Gratin de Macaronis</h2>
    <p>
      The French transform macaroni and cheese into a rich baked gratin
      topped with buttery breadcrumbs and aged cheeses like gruyère.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="country-card">
    <img src="/images/uk-mac-and-cheese.jpg" alt="British macaroni cheese">
    <h2>🇬🇧 United Kingdom – Macaroni Cheese</h2>
    <p>
      Popular in pubs and homes alike, the British version is often
      topped with cheddar and breadcrumbs and baked until bubbling.
    </p>
  </div>

</section>

</main>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>